The paper deals with repair semantics in ontology-based data access, which is a topic that falls under the intersection of several subfields of computer science. The use of syntactic distance to cluster repairs is a technique that is commonly used in artificial intelligence and machine learning, hence the high likelihood of cs.AI. The paper also deals with databases and reasoning, which are topics that fall under cs.DB and cs.LO respectively. The paper proposes a generic framework, which involves software engineering techniques, hence the likelihood of cs.SE. Finally, the paper deals with reasoning with several repairs, which is a topic that falls under cs.CC (computational complexity).
